cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.CR 

The paper deals with a computer vision problem of pedestrian re-identification and proposes a novel attention mechanism for deep learning frameworks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the learning process and the use of synthetic data, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of class information and the focus on foreground samples indicate that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper deals with image and video data, which suggests that it could belong to cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper discusses the effectiveness of the proposed solution in comparison to state-of-the-art techniques, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
